00:42:46.260 --> 00:42:50.030
&gt;&gt; So what's your number one
way to handle writer's block?

00:42:50.030 --> 00:42:51.580
&gt;&gt; Alexandra Bracken:
My number one way

00:42:51.580 --> 00:42:52.940
of handling writer's block?

00:42:52.940 --> 00:42:54.240
Was that the question?

00:42:54.240 --> 00:42:55.540
&gt;&gt; Yeah.

00:42:55.540 --> 00:42:56.840
&gt;&gt; Alexandra Bracken: Okay.

00:42:56.840 --> 00:42:59.670
I -- so writer's
block is so pesky.

00:42:59.670 --> 00:43:03.570
It really -- you really
do almost have to figure

00:43:03.570 --> 00:43:04.990
out your own way of handling it.

00:43:04.990 --> 00:43:07.200
But what I have noticed
for myself is

00:43:07.200 --> 00:43:09.590
that when I hit writer's block,

00:43:09.590 --> 00:43:12.420
it's because I am ignoring
something that is not working

00:43:12.420 --> 00:43:15.050
in the story and I don't
want to like confront it.

00:43:15.050 --> 00:43:19.430
So I -- even though it's
counterintuitive, I stop working

00:43:19.430 --> 00:43:21.670
and I go back and re-read
through what I have.

00:43:21.670 --> 00:43:24.810
And if -- and try to figure out
what it is that is not working.

00:43:24.810 --> 00:43:28.080
But sometimes, if it's just
I can't focus on that day

00:43:28.080 --> 00:43:30.470
or I'm stumped about how
to write it, you know,

00:43:30.470 --> 00:43:32.600
what to write next in
that particular scene

00:43:32.600 --> 00:43:35.170
or for the dialogue, I switch.

00:43:35.170 --> 00:43:36.720
I switch mediums.

00:43:36.720 --> 00:43:41.030
I'll start writing by hand which
I don't know the psychology

00:43:41.030 --> 00:43:42.930
of this but it kind of does
something to your brain

00:43:42.930 --> 00:43:46.130
to either change the way
you're writing or move

00:43:46.130 --> 00:43:47.450
like physically move yourself

00:43:47.450 --> 00:43:49.080
to a different location
and write there.

00:43:49.080 --> 00:43:50.710
Sometimes, that shakes
things loose.

00:43:50.710 --> 00:43:52.010
You wouldn't think so but --

00:43:52.010 --> 00:43:53.880
and sometimes, even
just free writing

00:43:53.880 --> 00:43:57.500
in a journal is a great way
to kind of unstick yourself.

00:43:57.500 --> 00:43:58.800
So try those.

00:43:58.800 --> 00:44:01.140
Always keep like a -- I have my
little writer's block journal

00:44:01.140 --> 00:44:03.410
where I just write
and write and write.

00:44:03.410 --> 00:44:05.880
And it's all nonsense
but it's a great way

00:44:05.880 --> 00:44:08.790
to shake yourself out of that.

